      <div rendition="class:83225 maturity:83211" type="edition" xml:lang="san-Latn">
        <!--
Comments below by Csaba Kiss and Dániel Balogh (BD) are offered "as is" and do not represent a thoroughly researched or considered opinion.
-->
        <!--
1 Katare, S.L., 'Sirpur plates of Mahā-Sudevarāja',
Epigraphia Indica vol XXXI, pp. 103-108
2 Shastri, A. M., Inscriptions of the Śarabhapurīyas,
Pāṇḍuvaṁśins and Somavaṁśins, Part II Inscriptions,
Motilal Bandarsidass, Delhi, 1995, pp. 35-38
-->
        <div n="A" type="textpart">
          <head xml:lang="eng">Seal</head>
          <lg met="anuṣṭubh" n="1">
            <lb n="1"/>
            <l n="a">prasanna-tanayasyedaṁ</l>
            <l n="b">vikkramotkhāta-vidviṣa<supplied reason="omitted">ḥ</supplied></l>
            <lb n="2"/>
            <l n="c">śrīmato jayarājasya</l>
            <l n="d">śāsanaṁ ripu-śāsana<choice>
                <sic>
                  <unclear>ṁ</unclear>
                </sic>
                <corr>M</corr>
              </choice></l>
            <!--
Katare thinks that that seal originally belonged to another
set of copper plates. The Ed. disagrees. Shastri cites other opinions
and finally agrees with Katare.
-->
          </lg>
        </div>
        <div n="B" type="textpart">
          <head xml:lang="eng">Plates</head>
          <p><pb n="1v"/><lb n="1"/><g type="mangala"/>
svasti<supplied reason="subaudible">.</supplied>
śarabha-purād vikkramopanata-sāmanta-ma<supplied evidence="parallel" reason="lost">kuṭa-cūḍā-maṇi</supplied>-
<lb n="2"/>prabhā-prasekāmbu-dhauta-pāda-yugalo ripu-vilāsi<supplied evidence="parallel" reason="lost">nī-sīmantoddharaṇa</supplied>-
<lb n="3"/>hetur vvasu-vasudhā-go-pradaḫ parama-bhāgava<supplied evidence="parallel" reason="lost">to mātā-pitr̥-pādā</supplied><lb break="no" n="4"/>nuddhyātaś śrī-mahā-sudeva-rājaḥ
						<choice>
              <unclear>c</unclear>
              <unclear>v</unclear>
            </choice>u<gap precision="low" quantity="9" reason="lost" unit="character"/><!--
Katare reads vu here, Shastri cu. Name of donated village and district lost. D. Balogh: cu seems more likely; elsewhere in these plates v consistently appears to have a square body, c an oblong one.
--><lb break="no" n="5"/>vake prativāsi-kuṭumbinas samājñā<supplied evidence="parallel" reason="lost">payati| viditam astu vo</supplied><!--
L5. Village is "Keśavaka" says Shastri.
--><!--
L5. ā in samājñ- is "is indicated by the downward elongation of the right
vertical of the letter m". Shastri
--><lb n="6"/>yathāsmābhir ayaṁ grāmas
t<choice>
              <sic>r̥</sic>
              <corr>ri</corr>
            </choice>daśapati-sa<supplied evidence="parallel" reason="lost">dana-sukha-pratiṣṭhā-karo</supplied>
						<pb n="2r"/><lb n="7"/>yāvad ravi-śaśi-tārā-kiraṇa-pratihata-ghorāndhakāraṁ jagad avatiṣṭha<lb break="no" n="8"/>te tāvad upabhogyas sanidhis sopanidhir
acāṭa-bhaṭa-prāveśyas sarvva-ka<lb break="no" n="9"/>ra-visarjjita<supplied reason="omitted">ḥ</supplied> pūrvvaṁ
nanna-pādais taittirīya-pārāśara-sagotra-brāhma<lb break="no" n="10"/>ṇa-kāraṇika-kansippasvāmin<choice>
              <sic>o</sic>
              <corr>e</corr>
            </choice><!--
L10. Both Shastri and Katare emend to svāmine.
-->datta Idānīm apy asmābhir api
<lb n="11"/>mahā-devī-rāja-kulānāṁ vijñāpyā<choice>
              <sic>s</sic>
              <corr>t</corr>
            </choice><!--
L11. Katare emends to vijñāpyāt. Shastri: "Read: vijñāpya tāmra-"
-->tām<surplus>b</surplus>ra-śāsanī-kr̥taḥ te yūyaṁ E<lb break="no" n="12"/>vam upalabhyāsyājñā-śravaṇa-vidheyā bhūtvā yathocitaṁ bhoga-bhāga<pb break="no" n="2v"/><lb break="no" n="13"/>m upanayantas sukhaṁ prativatsyatha<supplied reason="subaudible">.</supplied><!--
L13. Katare emends to prativatsatha.
-->bhaviṣyataś ca bhūmipān anu<lb break="no" n="14"/>darśayati|
</p>
          <lg met="vasantatilakā" n="1">
            <l n="a">dānād viśiṣṭam anupālana-jaṁ purāṇā</l>
            <l n="b">dharmmeṣu niścita-
<lb n="15"/>dhiyaḫ pravadanti dharmma<choice>
                <sic>ṁ</sic>
                <corr>M</corr>
              </choice></l>
            <l n="c">tasmā<supplied reason="omitted">d</supplied> dvijāya su-viśuddha-kula-śrutāya</l>
            <l n="d">dattāṁ<!--
L15. Shastri suggests "tasmād [d*] dvijāya", which must be a typo.
--><lb n="16"/>bhuvaṁ bhavatu vo matir eva goptu<supplied reason="omitted">M</supplied>||</l>
          </lg>
          <p>tad bhavadbhir apy eṣā dattir anu<lb break="no" n="17"/>pālay<choice>
              <sic>ī</sic>
              <corr>i</corr>
            </choice>tavyā<!--
Katare reads anupālayitavyā.
-->vyāsa-gītāṁś cātra ślokān udāharanti</p>
          <lg met="indravajrā" n="2">
            <!--
Garuḍapurāṇa 2.42.4
-->
            <l n="a">agner apatyaṁ pra<lb break="no" n="18"/>thamaṁ suvarṇṇaṁ</l>
            <l n="b">bhūr vvaiṣṇavī sūryya-sutāś ca gāvaḥ</l>
            <l n="c">dattās trayas te
								<pb break="no" n="3r"/>
<lb break="no" n="19"/>na bhavanti lokā<surplus>ḥ</surplus></l>
            <l n="d">yaẖ kāñcanaṁ gāṁ ca mahī<unclear>ṁ</unclear> ca dadyāt</l>
            <!--
L19. In Shastri, ṁ is not unclear; it is supplied. D. Balogh: I see no trace of anusvāra in the facsimile in EI, but we can give the engraver the benefit of doubt.
-->
          </lg>
          <lg met="anuṣṭubh" n="3">
            <l n="a">ṣaṣṭi-varṣa-sa<lb break="no" n="20"/>hasrāṇi</l>
            <l n="b">svargge modati bhūmi-daḥ</l>
            <l n="c">Acchettā cānumantā ca</l>
            <l n="d">tāny e<lb break="no" n="21"/>va narake vaseT</l>
          </lg>
          <lg met="anuṣṭubh" n="4">
            <l n="a">bahubhir vvasudhā dattā</l>
            <l n="b">rājabhis sagarādibhiḥ</l>
            <l n="c">yasya <lb break="no" n="22"/>yasya yadā
bhūmi<choice>
                <sic>ḥ</sic>
                <corr>s</corr>
              </choice></l>
            <l n="d">tasya tasya tadā phala<choice>
                <sic>ṁ</sic>
                <corr>M</corr>
              </choice></l>
          </lg>
          <lg met="anuṣṭubh" n="5">
            <l n="a">sva-dattāṁ para-dattāṁ vā</l>
            <l n="b"><lb n="23"/>yatnād rakṣa yudhiṣṭhira</l>
            <l n="c">mahī<choice>
                <sic>t</sic>
                <corr>ṁ</corr>
              </choice>
mahimatāñ śreṣṭha</l>
            <!--
v5c. In other inscriptions others correct it, probably wrongly, to mahīmatāṁ.
-->
            <l n="d">dānāc chreyo <supplied reason="subaudible">’</supplied>nupāla
<lb break="no" n="24"/>nam</l>
          </lg>
          <p>iti<supplied reason="subaudible">.</supplied> sva-mukhājñayā
pravarddhamāna-v<choice>
              <sic>ī</sic>
              <corr>i</corr>
            </choice>jaya-sa<choice>
              <sic>v</sic>
              <corr>ṁ</corr>
            </choice>va <num value="7">7</num> dvi-bhādra-di <num value="10">
              <g type="numeral">10</g>
            </num></p>
          <p><pb n="3v"/><lb n="25"/>U<choice>
              <sic>kt</sic>
              <corr>tk</corr>
            </choice>īrṇṇaṁ droṇasi<choice>
              <sic>ṅgh</sic>
              <corr>ṁh</corr>
            </choice>e<choice>
              <sic>ṇ</sic>
              <corr>n</corr>
            </choice>a||<!--
L25. This is engraved in the middle of the plate.
--></p>
        </div>
      </div>
